Moodie/Traill for Laurie

Here are some pix I've come across that may be of interest. The 'cabin' ones are taken out here at Uncle Clarence's (now Uncle Jim's) woodlot. Clarence cleared a space big enough for the cabin in the middle of trees and it might be a good background. It's accessible any time of year. Rick and his buddies used to stop there for coffee (??? hmmm) when out snowmobiling and it's the world's best source of pinecones for any and all purposes. I'm sure you will have seen some of the others already. I've just borrowd back my g-g-g-grandmother's log cabin quilt (from my daughter) in case you want to use it as a reference. It's the right era and would have been made right here in the area. Erica says you are welcome to study and/or photograph it. Enjoy!
